        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 9:06PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 905 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Madison Heights, or near Concord, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lynchburg...
Buckingham...
Appomattox...
Dillwyn...
Bent Creek...
Concord...
and Madison Heights.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
central Virginia.</instruction>
